```

**Key .NET 11 APIs used:**

| Method | Returns | Throws if missing? |
|--------|---------|-------------------|
| `options.GetTypeInfo<T>()` | `JsonTypeInfo<T>` | ✅ Yes |
| `options.TryGetTypeInfo<T>(out ...)` | `bool` | ❌ No |

`TryGetTypeInfo<T>` is the no-exception path — returns `false` when the resolver doesn't know about `T`, so you can branch cleanly without `try/catch`.
